        <hl1>Global Warming: The Will to Act</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John Sitter letter says honest and informed attention to human population growth must be part of any solution to global warming (March 5 Nicholas D Kristof Op-Ed column)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Nicholas D. Kristof rightly calls for immediate conservation and rapid shifts to cleaner and renewable energy sources to address global warming. But honest and informed attention to human population growth must be part of any solution.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Nicholas D. Kristof rightly calls for immediate conservation and rapid shifts to cleaner and renewable energy sources to address global warming. But honest and informed attention to human population growth must be part of any solution.</p>
        <p>Global population now increases at the rate of 200,000 a day, or more than 8,000 an hour. Will this generation be forgiven for frustrating rather than encouraging access to birth control and family planning?</p>
        <p>John Sitter  Notre Dame, Ind., March 6, 2006</p>
      </block>
